          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634047503450-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Combine the <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>honey mustard sauce</strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634047508697-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634047508697-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634047508697-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634047508697-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634047508697-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 15 min, remove the sausages from the oven and drizzle the <strong>honey mustard sauce </strong>over the top</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a final 10-12 min or until the sausages are cooked through and the sauce is sticky – these are your <strong>bonfire bangers</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix </strong>in 200ml [350ml] <strong>boiled water </strong>with the <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> – this is your <strong>beefy tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634047729254-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634047729254-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634047729254-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634047729254-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634047729254-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>caramelised red onion</strong> from the pan and set aside</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and once melted, add  1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min until a sandy paste forms</p><p>Add the <strong>beefy tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> then whisk until combined and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>beefy tomato gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1634047738672-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1634047738672-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
